headline: Worried About a Stock Market Sell-Off in 2025? Consider Buying This Ultra-Safe Vanguard ETF in December.
summary: Volatility spiked in the broader indexes after the Federal Reserve indicated that it could keep interest rates higher for longer.  The Vanguard U.S. Minimum Volatility ETF (NYSEMKT: VFMV) has a mere 0.13% expense ratio, or $1.30 for every $1,000 invested.  The Vanguard U.S. Minimum Volatility ETF targets super-safe companies, many of which pay dividends.
